definitions.definition: The way things are , the totality of all things in the physical universe and their order , especially the physical world in contrast to spiritual realms and flora and fauna as distinct from human conventions , art , and technology .
examples: The laws of nature are written in the language of mathematics .
Tectonic activity is part of nature , so there's no way to stop earthquakes.

definitions.definition: The particular way someone or something is , especially

subdefinitions.definition: The essential or innate characteristics of a person or thing which will always tend to manifest , especially in contrast to specific contexts , reason , religious duty , upbringing , and personal pretense or effort .
examples: It's not in my nature to steal.
You can't help feeling that way. It's human nature .
Power corrupts . That's just the nature of the beast .

subdefinitions.definition: The distinguishing characteristic of a person or thing, understood as its general class, sort, type, etc.
examples: What was the nature of your relationship with the deceased?
The best medium might be petroleum, liquified gas, or something of that nature .

subdefinitions.definition: Synonym of caliber : the class of a gun .

definitions.definition: The vital functions or strength of someone or something , especially ( now dialect ) as requiring nourishment or careful maintenance or ( medicine ) as a force of regeneration without special treatment .
A requirement or powerful impulse of the body 's physical form , especially

subdefinitions.definition: The need to urinate and defecate .
examples: I hear the call of nature .

subdefinitions.definition: Spontaneous love , affection , or reverence , especially between parent and child .
subdefinitions.label_groups: now chiefly UK regional and African-American Vernacular

definitions.definition: A product of the body 's physical form , especially semen and vaginal fluids , menstrual fluid , and ( obsolete ) feces .
A part of the body 's physical form , especially ( obsolete ) the female genitalia .
